&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;questlistid&gt;Soular002&lt;/questlistid&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Investigating Weed Ridge&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Collecting Dodo&amp;amp;#039;s marrow from Little Dodo&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Cardiff Island was a land, where all different lives lived in perfect balance.

Lately, the number of Dodo, a monster living in Weed Ridge, got larger. They even turned out being violent, and sometimes come close to the village and attack civilians.

Thus the civilians started to hate the Dodo... the leader of Roxbury Civilian Association, Blacksmith Mark, even insists on killing them all.
As a member of the Divine Association I cannot let them kill each other.

We need to contact the fairies, to know what happened to Dodo. Please go out and collect Little Dodo&amp;amp;#039;s Marrow.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;The movements of the village people are mysterious. We have to do something about it.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Thank you! Thanks to you, we will be able to contact the Dodo&amp;amp;#039;s spirits. I hope the reason will come out soon. Thank you for the hard work.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;questlistid&gt;Soular002&lt;/questlistid&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Investigating Weed Ridge&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Collecting Dodo&amp;amp;#039;s marrow from Little Dodo&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Cardiff Island was a land, where all different lives lived in perfect balance.

Lately, the number of Dodo, a monster living in Weed Ridge, got larger. They even turned out being violent, and sometimes come close to the village and attack civilians.

&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;The movements of the village people are mysterious. We have to do something about it.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Thank you! Thanks to you, we will be able to contact the Dodo&amp;amp;#039;s spirits. I hope the reason will come out soon. Thank you for the hard work.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></soular002><soular003><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;questlistid&gt;Soular003&lt;/questlistid&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Solving of Misunderstanding&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Conversation with Mark, the blacksmith&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;We succeeded to read the Dodo&amp;amp;rsquo;s memories from what you brought to us.

These Dodos are not from Weed Ridge. They are from Larksdowns. Larksdowns&amp;amp;rsquo; Dodos looked larger because they were chased by something, frightened and came into Weed Ridge. The fairies&amp;amp;rsquo; memories were too complicated to read the exact reasons why they came in&amp;amp;hellip;.

Mark, the leader of Weed Ridge Civil Association, is going to ask to Landlord to hunt Dodos with his guards. But hunting Dodos is not the answer. If we don&amp;amp;rsquo;t know what was chasing them, other Dodos will come and hurt people. You can find Blacksmith Mark near by the door to Weed Ridge. Tell Mark what I told you, please.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;You haven&amp;amp;#039;t delivered my message yet? You can find Mark near the door which leads you to Weedridge. Please hurry up!&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Hmm&amp;amp;hellip; So you are saying killing all of them is not going to solve the problems. I see&amp;amp;hellip; since the words are from the Divine Association Master, I will tell the citizens to hunt them as long as protecting their properties, but I cannot promise you what happen to next time as dodo&amp;amp;#039;s behavior become severe. You have to remember that.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
