&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;questlistid&gt;ac1gt005&lt;/questlistid&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Paying Tax Properly&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Take the tax to Anais&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;I&amp;amp;#039;ve finished calculating taxes, receipts and payments based on the account books of the merchants of Roxbury.
Hmm&amp;amp;hellip; This time the payment is quite big. Trade has been done actively, thanks to the increase of users. If it keeps going like this, the Florensia Kingdom will be financially abundant. They&amp;amp;#039;ll need a large budget to organize the 6th Royal Search Party and I hope this tax helps. The king should come back as soon as possible so that Princess Angelina can be free from the Noble Masquer.

Now, now. Hurry and deliver this money to the bank clerk Anais at the Roxbury Bank. I&amp;amp;#039;ll tell Anais to pay you after the tax has been paid.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Why are you still here when I&amp;amp;#039;ve already asked you to pay the tax? To go to the bank turn left from the trading post and go up a little bit. Anais will be there.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Jeremiah has paid the taxes right on time as usual. The members of the merchant union Magistri are very punctual and have a good sense of money.  I&amp;amp;#039;ll give you the pay Jeremiah promised since I&amp;amp;#039;ve received the taxes.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
