When you are moving out in the sea, you will encounter plenty of pirates, as well as sea monsters. To be able to combat them, you must know how to load cannon balls.

Cannon balls can be simply loaded in the inventory, similar to your weapons.

First, click the inventory icon to open the inventory menu box. Ah-ha, you forgot which one it is, didn&amp;amp;#039;t you? It&amp;amp;#039;s the bag-shaped icon on your right.

Now, in the inventory menu box, you will find [Small-sized Metallic Shot for Training]. Drag the mouse to [Small-sized Metallic Shot for Training], and right-click. After doing this, the menu box will change into the battle ship, showing the cannon ball loaded over the left side. You were surprised because the inventory menu box was changed suddenly? Don&amp;amp;#039;t worry about that. You can see loaded weapons for the warship or for the character, whenever you click the [Land&amp;amp;lt;-&amp;amp;gt;Sea] icon on the right center of the inventory menu box.

Now try it.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;You can come to me any time, if you need a ship or ship&amp;amp;#039;s body parts. I will give you a good deal.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Good job. Now, you can go out to the sea.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
